# Adding a shadcn Component

## Install

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <name>
```

The CLI drops the component at `components/ui/<name>.jsx`. Do **not** move it
into `components/ui/magic/` — `magic/` is reserved for Magic UI.

## After install

1. Re-export from `components/ui/index.js` (alphabetical):
   ```js
   export * from "./<name>"
   ```

2. Add a demo file `components/demo/components/<name>.jsx` exporting at least
   `<Name>Demo`. Include `<Name>DemoStart` for a minimal example and any
   relevant variants (`<Name>Demo<Modifier>`).

3. Re-export from `components/demo/components/index.js`.

4. Add the component to the section list in
   `app/demo/components/page.jsx` (it's a data-driven page; just append a new
   entry to the `sections` array with `id`, `name`, `slug`, `file`,
   `description`, and `variants`).

5. Add the `id` to the `components` items array in
   `components/showcase/manifest.js` so the global command palette finds it.

## Conventions

- **Don't fork** shadcn primitives — extend via wrappers in your own folder
  if needed (e.g. `components/forms/`).
- All variants must be `"use client"`-clean unless they require it.
- Match shadcn naming exactly — file names, export names, slot data attributes.
